{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-documentation-tsx","path":"/docs/handbook/epoch-ide","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"701fd411-be28-57bc-b1af-acab8f85cf1d","excerpt":"This page shows how to install and run the Epoch integrated development environment (IDE). Epoch is a standalone application based on Eclipse that provides a…","html":"<p>This page shows how to install and run the Epoch integrated development environment (IDE). Epoch is a standalone application based on Eclipse that provides a syntax-directed editor, compiler, and diagram synthesis tool for Lingua Franca programs.</p>\n<h2 id=\"download-epoch\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#download-epoch\" aria-label=\"download epoch permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Download Epoch</h2>\n<p>Download the appropriate <code>epoch_ide_...</code> file for your platform from:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/lf-lang/lingua-franca/releases/tag/v0.3.0\">Version 0.3.0</a> (the most recent release)</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/lf-lang/lingua-franca/releases/tag/nightly\">Nightly build</a> (the latest prerelease, unstable)</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"set-up-epoch-in-macos\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#set-up-epoch-in-macos\" aria-label=\"set up epoch in macos permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Set Up Epoch in MacOS</h2>\n<p>The downloaded file is a compressed tarball. Open it to get an <code>epoch.app</code> item that you can drag into your <code>Applications</code> folder.</p>\n<p><strong>First</strong>: Currently, the Epoch IDE is not signed, and macOS will report it as “damaged” if you try to invoke it immediately. You can work around this by opening a terminal and running the following command:</p>\n<pre class=\"source-lf language-sh\"><span class=\"source-shell meta-statement-shell meta-command-shell entity-name-command-shell\">xattr</span><span class=\"source-shell meta-statement-shell meta-command-shell\"> </span><span class=\"source-shell meta-statement-shell meta-command-shell string-unquoted-argument-shell constant-other-option-dash-shell\">-</span><span class=\"source-shell meta-statement-shell meta-command-shell string-unquoted-argument constant-other-option\">cr</span><span class=\"source-shell meta-statement-shell meta-command-shell meta-argument-shell\"> </span><span class=\"source-shell meta-statement-shell meta-command-shell meta-argument-shell string-unquoted-argument-shell\">epoch.app</span>\n</pre>\n<p><strong>Second</strong>: By default, the Lingua Franca compiler uses <code>cmake</code> to compile the programs it generates. This is not installed by default on macOS systems. To install <code>cmake</code> using <code>brew</code>, just do this:</p>\n<pre class=\"source-lf language-sh\"><span class=\"source-shell meta-statement-shell meta-command-shell entity-name-command-shell\">brew</span><span class=\"source-shell meta-statement-shell meta-command-shell meta-argument-shell\"> </span><span class=\"source-shell meta-statement-shell meta-command-shell meta-argument-shell string-unquoted-argument-shell\">install</span><span class=\"source-shell meta-statement-shell meta-command-shell meta-argument-shell\"> </span><span class=\"source-shell meta-statement-shell meta-command-shell meta-argument-shell string-unquoted-argument-shell\">cmake</span>\n</pre>\n<p>Verify that cmake is in your path by typing <code>which cmake</code>.</p>\n<p><strong>Third</strong>: We recommend also starting Epoch from the command line because then it will inherit your <code>PATH</code> variable (If you start it by double clicking on the icon, as usual in macOS, it will not find <code>cmake</code> and will be unable to build LF programs). To do this, in a terminal window:</p>\n<pre class=\"source-lf language-sh\"><span class=\"source-shell meta-statement-shell meta-command-shell entity-name-command-shell\">open</span><span class=\"source-shell meta-statement-shell meta-command-shell meta-argument-shell\"> </span><span class=\"source-shell meta-statement-shell meta-command-shell meta-argument-shell string-unquoted-argument-shell\">epoch.app</span>\n</pre>\n<p>If you instead start Epoch by double clicking on its icon, then when you compile Lingua Franca programs, you may get unexpected results or unexpected failures because Epoch fails to find required programs (e.g., your python runtime system or a compiler) or finds a different version from what <code>lfc</code> will find.</p>\n<p><strong>Fourth</strong>: By default, Epoch is set to “Build Automatically” in the Project menu. This means that the LF code generator and compiler will be invoked every time you change a file and whenever you open a new project (on all files in the project). Many people prefer to turn this feature off and invoke the code generator by hand by clicking on the gear icon at the upper left.</p>\n<h2 id=\"set-up-epoch-in-linux\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#set-up-epoch-in-linux\" aria-label=\"set up epoch in linux permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Set Up Epoch in Linux</h2>\n<p><strong>First</strong>: Uncompress the download (shown assuming the 0.3.0 version):</p>\n<pre class=\"source-lf language-sh\"><span class=\"source-shell meta-statement-shell meta-command-shell entity-name-command-shell\">tar</span><span class=\"source-shell meta-statement-shell meta-command-shell meta-argument-shell\"> </span><span class=\"source-shell meta-statement-shell meta-command-shell meta-argument-shell string-unquoted-argument-shell\">xvf</span><span class=\"source-shell meta-statement-shell meta-command-shell meta-argument-shell\"> </span><span class=\"source-shell meta-statement-shell meta-command-shell meta-argument-shell string-unquoted-argument-shell\">epoch_ide_0.</span><span class=\"source-shell meta-statement-shell meta-command-shell meta-argument-shell string-unquoted-argument-shell constant-numeric-decimal-shell\">3</span><span class=\"source-shell meta-statement-shell meta-command-shell meta-argument-shell string-unquoted-argument-shell constant-numeric-decimal-point-shell\">.</span><span class=\"source-shell meta-statement-shell meta-command-shell meta-argument-shell string-unquoted-argument-shell constant-numeric-decimal-shell\">0</span><span class=\"source-shell meta-statement-shell meta-command-shell meta-argument-shell string-unquoted-argument-shell\">-linux.gtk.x86_64.tar.gz</span>\n</pre>\n<p><strong>Second</strong>: Find and execute the IDE:</p>\n<pre class=\"source-lf language-sh\"><span class=\"source-shell meta-statement-shell meta-command-shell entity-name-command-shell support-function-builtin-shell\">cd</span><span class=\"source-shell meta-statement-shell meta-command-shell meta-argument-shell\"> </span><span class=\"source-shell meta-statement-shell meta-command-shell meta-argument-shell string-unquoted-argument-shell\">epoch_ide_0.</span><span class=\"source-shell meta-statement-shell meta-command-shell meta-argument-shell string-unquoted-argument-shell constant-numeric-decimal-shell\">3</span><span class=\"source-shell meta-statement-shell meta-command-shell meta-argument-shell string-unquoted-argument-shell constant-numeric-decimal-point-shell\">.</span><span class=\"source-shell meta-statement-shell meta-command-shell meta-argument-shell string-unquoted-argument-shell constant-numeric-decimal-shell\">0</span><span class=\"source-shell meta-statement-shell meta-command-shell meta-argument-shell string-unquoted-argument-shell\">-linux.gtk.x86_64</span>\n<span class=\"source-shell meta-statement-shell meta-command-shell entity-name-command-shell support-function-builtin-shell\">.</span><span class=\"source-shell meta-statement-shell meta-command-shell entity-name-command-shell\">/epoch</span>\n</pre>\n<p>You can move this executable to a more convenient place, ideally somewhere in your <code>PATH</code>.</p>\n<h2 id=\"set-up-epoch-in-windows\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#set-up-epoch-in-windows\" aria-label=\"set up epoch in windows permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Set Up Epoch in Windows</h2>\n<p><strong>First</strong>: In a terminal,</p>\n<pre class=\"source-lf language-powershell\"><span class=\"source-powershell\">unzip epoch_ide_0.</span><span class=\"source-powershell constant-numeric-integer-powershell\">3.0</span><span class=\"source-powershell keyword-operator-assignment-powershell\">-</span><span class=\"source-powershell\">win32.win32.x86_64.zip</span>\n<span class=\"source-powershell\">cd epoch_ide_0.</span><span class=\"source-powershell constant-numeric-integer-powershell\">3.0</span><span class=\"source-powershell keyword-operator-assignment-powershell\">-</span><span class=\"source-powershell\">win32.win32.x86_64</span>\n<span class=\"source-powershell\">.\\epoch</span>\n</pre>","headings":[{"value":"Download Epoch","depth":2},{"value":"Set Up Epoch in MacOS","depth":2},{"value":"Set Up Epoch in Linux","depth":2},{"value":"Set Up Epoch in Windows","depth":2}],"frontmatter":{"permalink":"/docs/handbook/epoch-ide","title":"Epoch IDE","oneline":"Epoch IDE for Lingua Franca.","preamble":""}},"prev":{"childMarkdownRemark":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Code Extension","oneline":"Visual Studio Code Extension for Lingua Franca.","permalink":"/docs/handbook/code-extension"}}},"next":{"childMarkdownRemark":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Command Line Tools","oneline":"Command-line tools for Lingua Franca.","permalink":"/docs/handbook/command-line-tools"}}}},"pageContext":{"id":"2-epoch-ide","slug":"/docs/handbook/epoch-ide","repoPath":"/packages/documentation/copy/en/tools/Epoch IDE.md","previousID":"235f1196-3f3d-57bd-a2f6-22ac00082f94","nextID":"3843375e-c15b-5455-8678-0c0fa5f6264e","lang":"en","modifiedTime":"2023-02-02T05:17:06.875Z"}},"staticQueryHashes":[]}